Gives an overview about the essence of strategic management and its role in an enterprise, as well as about the developing of strategic thinking in the historical perspective. Emphasis is on strategic analysis, its different methods (SWOT analysis, portfolio analysis, competition analysis etc.) and on the possibilities of their usage, as well as the problems connected with it. Also the most spread contemporary management theories and conceptions are dealt with. This course gives knowledge and practical experience of strategic management, which enables better to manage the organization.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of this course is to develop knowledge and skills about strategic management concepts and methods.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) has knowledge about main concepts of strategic management and is able to understand  theoretical and practical issues of strategic management; 2) knows the techniques and methods of strategic analysis of an organization; 3) has skills to conduct strategic analysis of the organization and its environment and is able to evaluate the appropriateness of different competition strategies; 4) has conducted strategic analysis and developed strategic plan of a particular organization 5) has acquired practical experience in strategic management within the organization.
